  "prompt": "Are there other movies like The Secret?",
  "response": "If you enjoyed \"The Secret\" and are looking for similar movies that delve into themes of personal empowerment, self-help, and the law of attraction, here are some recommendations:\n\n1. **The Secret: Dare to Dream (2020)**\n   - A narrative film based on the principles of \"The Secret,\" focusing on a widow whose life changes after meeting a man who introduces her to the power of positive thinking.\n\n2. **What the Bleep Do We Know!? (2004)**\n   - A blend of narrative and documentary that explores the intersection of science and spirituality, touching on quantum physics and how our thoughts impact our reality.\n\n3. **The Shift (2009)**\n   - Featuring Dr. Wayne Dyer, this film discusses the shift from an ego-driven life to a more meaningful existence, incorporating principles similar to those in \"The Secret.\"\n\n4. **You Can Heal Your Life (2007)**\n   - Based on the work of Louise Hay, this film delves into the power of positive thinking and affirmations to transform one's life, akin to the principles taught in \"The Secret.\"\n\n5. **The Power of the Heart (2014)**\n   - A documentary that explores how heart-centered living can transform lives, featuring interviews with thought leaders in spirituality and personal development.\n\n6. **The Law of Attraction (2006)**\n   - A documentary that explicitly focuses on the law of attraction, explaining how to use it to achieve personal goals and desires.\n\n7. **Leap! (2016)**\n   - An animated film that, while not a documentary, embodies the spirit of \"The Secret\" with its message of following dreams and believing in oneself.\n\nThese movies offer a range of perspectives and approaches to similar themes, providing plenty of content for those interested in exploring the concepts further.",
